latestPosts.caption:
In the narrow bylanes of Lucknow, time slows down and thread by thread, stories are embroidered into one of the city’s oldest craft- Chikankari. From the whispered tales of Noor Jahan to the skilled hands keeping the art alive today, this is more than embroidery. 

Big thanks to @shotbyharshit for so effortlessly helping us find our way through Lucknow’s maze of culture and craft.

And to @visuals.kuxh , for capturing the magic behind the scenes. His creative eye, patience, and edits brought this story to life just the way it deserved.🌸

This video is just for fun lekin “GRWM or haul na banane ka ghammand hai”🙂‍↔️

#explore #explorepage #holyfknairball #fashion #outfitinspiration

There is a quiet legacy stitched into the fabric we wear. It is the legacy of hands that move with memory, of crafts honed over generations, and of cities whose soul lives in thread and needle. 

Kapdon Ki Kaarigari is a journey into this forgotten richness. It is a celebration of the artistry, time, and tradition that lie behind every garment. With every episode, I hope to remember that what we wear is not just fashion, but inheritance, history, and an age-old story✨
